ZH: 这家公司的股东们决定增加股本。
EN: The shareholders of this company have decided to increase its capital.

ZH: 股东会议将于下周举行。
EN: The shareholders' meeting will be held next week.

ZH: 他是这家公司的最大股东。
EN: He is the largest shareholder of this company.

ZH: 范先生是公司的股东之一。
EN: Mr. Fan is one of the shareholders of the company.

ZH: 股东们一致同意进行股权转让。
EN: The shareholders unanimously agreed to transfer their shares.

ZH: 公司前股东决定出售手中的股票。
EN: The former shareholders of the company decided to sell their shares.

ZH: 股东应该积极参与公司的决策。
EN: Shareholders should actively participate in the company's decision-making.

ZH: 老板明天要和股东开会。
EN: The boss is meeting with the shareholders tomorrow.

ZH: 公司的股东有权决定任何重大事项。
EN: Shareholders of the company have the right to decide on any major matters.

ZH: 股东们对公司的未来发展充满信心。
EN: Shareholders are confident about the company's future development.

ZH: 股东们需要签署文件以转让股权。
EN: Shareholders need to sign documents to transfer their shares.

ZH: 这位投资者是公司的新股东。
EN: This investor is the new shareholder of the company.

ZH: 董事会将与所有股东进行沟通。
EN: The board of directors will communicate with all shareholders.

ZH: 股东们对公司的业绩感到满意。
EN: Shareholders are satisfied with the company's performance.

ZH: 新股东要求对公司财务状况进行审计。
EN: The new shareholder requested an audit of the company's financial situation.

ZH: 股东们有责任保护公司的利益。
EN: Shareholders have a responsibility to protect the interests of the company.

ZH: 股东们的意见在会议上引起了争议。
EN: The shareholders' opinions caused controversy at the meeting.

ZH: 公司的股东关系良好。
EN: The company's shareholder relations are good.

ZH: 股东们应该为公司的长期利益着想。
EN: Shareholders should consider the long-term interests of the company.

ZH: 公司董事会将邀请股东参加下次会议。
EN: The company's board of directors will invite shareholders to attend the next meeting.
